\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/hgm.good_prime}{Primes of good and bad reduction of a hypergeometric motive}}
\begin{definition}\label{hgm.good_prime}
\uses{hgm.conductor,hgm.motive,hgm.tame,hgm.wild}
A \textbf{prime of bad reduction} or \textbf{bad prime} of a \hyperref[hgm.motive]{hypergeometric motive} \(M\) is a prime dividing the \hyperref[hgm.conductor]{conductor} of \(M\). A bad prime is either \hyperref[hgm.tame]{tame} or \hyperref[hgm.wild]{wild}.

A \textbf{prime of good reduction} or \textbf{good prime} is a prime that is not a bad prime, i.e., a prime that does not divide the conductor.
\end{definition}
